    "text_1": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Golf Style Icons: Past vs. Present",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>From Arnie's Cardigans to Jason Day in Cropped Pants, How Golf Fashion Evolved Without Losing Its Swagger</strong></p><p>Let's be honest, golf has always had a style game. It's just... changed a lot. In the golden era of the sport, players like Arnold Palmer and Seve Ballesteros stepped onto the course with elegance that felt effortless. Their looks were polished, classic, and, for the time, incredibly cool. Fast-forward to today, and you've got players like Jason Day and Erik van Rooyen taking risks and rewriting the dress code entirely. Different eras, same energy.</p><p>So, what happens when you stack the legends against the disruptors? You get a story of tradition, rebellion, and really good knitwear.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_1",
        "text_1"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "alignment": "left",
        "enable_animation": true
      }
    },
