    "text_2": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Arnold Palmer: The King of Clean",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Arnie wasn't flashy but he knew how to dress. Think crisp polos, perfectly tailored cardigans, and those timeless pleated slacks. It wasn't about trend, it was about trust. His clothes said, \"I've been here before,\" and his swing usually confirmed it.</p><p>Palmer didn't need to overdo it, he let fit and polish do the talking. Today, you'll find echoes of his understated style in brands like <strong>RLX Ralph Lauren</strong> and <strong>KJUS</strong>, where modern fabrics meet timeless silhouettes.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_1",
        "text_1"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "alignment": "left",
        "enable_animation": true
      }
    },
