    "text_4": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Jason Day: Golf's Style Renaissance Man",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Now we flip the script. Jason Day in <strong>Malbon</strong>? That's not just an outfit, it's a statement. Cropped, tailored pants. Asymmetric quarter-zips. Wide-legged trousers. Day has gone from traditional Nike fits to fashion-forward looks that belong on the runway <em>and</em> the leaderboard.</p><p>His partnership with Malbon isn't just a rebrand, it's a signal that golf fashion is becoming a platform for expression, not just uniformity. The man makes a vest over a graphic tee look country club approved.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_1",
        "text_1"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "alignment": "left",
        "enable_animation": true
      }
    },
